Sentencas: A hierarchical nanostructured Pr6O11 phase, a potential electrocatalyst for the oxygen reduction reaction, is prepared for the first time by electrostatic spray deposition (ESD) on a GDC (Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 _ (delta)) electrolyte and evaluated as an Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell cathode.
Titulo: An efficient hierarchical nanostructured Pr6O11 electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Different and innovative microstructures are found to be related to the solvent composition, deposition time, nozzle to substrate distance, substrate temperature and solution flow rate.
Titulo: An efficient hierarchical nanostructured Pr6O11 electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Single phase Pr6O11 films crystallize in a Fm (3) over barm fluorite cubic structure after calcination at 700 degrees C for 2 h in air.
Titulo: An efficient hierarchical nanostructured Pr6O11 electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties are found to be strongly dependent on the microstructure of the cathode films.
Titulo: An efficient hierarchical nanostructured Pr6O11 electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A symmetrical cell based on the double layer architecture (a columnar-type active layer by ESD topped by a screen-printed current collector) cathode presents a low polarization resistance value of 0.02 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C. To the best of our knowledge, this Pr6O11 cathode shows the best performance reported to date for all SOFC cathode materials.
Titulo: An efficient hierarchical nanostructured Pr6O11 electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A single cell made of a commercial (Ni-3YSZ/Ni-8YSZ/8YSZ/GDC) half cell and this double layer cathode delivers a maximum power density of 500 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C. Moreover, Pr6O11 does not show any reactivity with GDC over 10 days in air at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: An efficient hierarchical nanostructured Pr6O11 electrode for solid oxide fuel cells
